    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Configurations or positions of heavenly bodies relative to one another, particularly as seen from planet earth and as interpreted or named by various cultures through time. For example, a constellation may include a number of fixed stars and planets grouped together within the outline of an imaginary figure traced on the face of the sky.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
